[These questions were refered to Mike Miller, who replied: - Mod.MHJ]
........
Date: Mon, 2 Feb 98 16:55:51 MST
From: Mike Miller <mike.miller@state.co.us>

Follow-up information as per your request:
Species:
elk = Rocky Mountain elk (_Cervus elaphus nelsoni_)
deer = _Odocoileus_ sp., primarily mule deer (_O. hemionus_), but also some
white-tailed deer (_O. virginianus_)
Transmission: Circumstantial evidence suggests lateral transmission. [The]
role of genetic factors remains under investigation. No TSEs [have been]
diagnosed in local carnivores examined to date.
--
Mike Miller
e-mail: mike.miller@state.co.us
[Thank you, Mike. - Mod.MHJ]

