From: Tim Sly <tsly@acs.ryerson.ca>

Is anyone from Health Canada listening? Where's Harvey Artsob when you
need him? If so, what are the rates of CWD in Canadian ungulates? Are we
looking?
The various species of deer, moose, and vast migratory herds of caribou,
represent an important biomass that has no regard for borders. Of
particular interest is the composition of any winter feeding assistance
(e.g. airdrops), and at the other end of the pipeline, are culled animals
examined for TSEs?
